FBIS4-13253 "drnes075_r_94002" FBIS-NES-94-075 Daily Report 18 Apr 1994 SOUTH ASIA India Additional Battalions To Combat `Terrorism' in Kashmir Additional Battalions To Combat `Terrorism' in Kashmir BK1804160494 Delhi All India Radio Network in English 1530 GMT 18 Apr 94 BK1804160494 Delhi All India Radio Network English BFN [Text] In Jammu and Kashmir, 40 more battalions of paramilitary forces are to be raised to combat the menace of terrorism. The state additional chief secretary, Mr. Mamhmudur Rahman, in an interview with Radio Kashmir said that the force will be equipped with sophisticated arms to effectively meet the terrorist threat.
